news.title: Gorakhpur: Record land allotment to GIDA, ₹5,800 crore investments in 2025
news.para: Gorakhpur, once overlooked by investors, is rapidly emerging as an industrial hub, attracting major national and multinational companies. GIDA reports a record allocation of 182 acres for 54 new units, representing ₹5,800 crore in capital investment and 8,500 jobs.

news.title: Mundhwa society residents question inclusion in slum rehabilitation plan in Pune
news.para: Residents of Sarvodaya Cooperative Housing Society in Mundhwa are protesting their society's inclusion as a slum in the 2017 development plan. They claim their land was wrongly classified, and residents falsely listed as slum dwellers. A complaint has been filed with the Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA). Residents fear the SRA project will reduce their living space.

news.title: Now, settle violations in pattayam land
news.para: The Kerala cabinet has approved rules to implement the Kerala Land Assignment (Amendment) Act, aiming to regularize violated pattayam land and permit regulated alternative uses. Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan stated the move resolves long-standing high-range issues, following broad consultations and unanimous assembly passage.

news.title: Lucknow development body's digital databank to help simplify map approval process
news.para: The Lucknow Development Authority has launched a digital databank to streamline map approvals, eliminating the need for multiple NOCs. This centralised system contains land records from various departments, enabling officials to quickly determine plot ownership. A two-week deadline has been set for external agency approvals; if no response is received, the LDA will proceed independently.

news.title: Bombay HC order 11 members of four dilapidated Vasai buildings to vacate, allow redevelopment
news.para: The Bombay High Court has mandated minority residents of four dilapidated buildings in Vasai West to vacate their flats, emphasizing that obstruction hinders redevelopment. The court acknowledged the majority's decision for redevelopment and cautioned the dissenting members against impeding the process.

news.title: Morbi ceramics industry wants GST reduced to 5%
news.para: The ceramics industry in Morbi, a major tile producer, is requesting a GST reduction. They want the rate lowered from 18% to 5%. The Morbi Ceramic Manufacturers Association argues tiles are a necessity, not a luxury. Lowering GST would help small businesses and boost related sectors. Trade bodies across India support this appeal to the Union finance minister.

news.title: Jet Airways to transfer Mumbai office space lease for ₹370 crore
news.para: Jet Airways, currently in liquidation after ceasing operations in 2019, has agreed to transfer the lease of its Mumbai office space to Parthos Properties Pvt Ltd for Rs 370.25 crore. This transfer, part of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code process following a Supreme Court order in November 2024, is pending approval from the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority.

news.title: Nagpur: I-T dept finds ‘selective’ under-reporting of realty deals transactions by sub registrars
news.para: An income tax probe in Nagpur has revealed selective underreporting of property transactions by sub-registrars' offices, particularly involving specific builders. Deals worth crores were not reported in the Statement of Financial Transactions, leading to scrutiny of thousands of taxpayers' returns. Property registrar officers have initiated an internal reconciliation of records.

news.title: Gaursons Group to mortgage mall to clear ₹315 crore dues for registry of over 2,000 flats
news.para: GNIDA has conditionally approved Gaursons Group's proposal to mortgage part of Gaur City Mall to secure farmer compensation dues. This move aims to enable the execution of approximately 2,100 pending sub-lease deeds across three housing projects, offering relief to residents awaiting legal ownership. An independent valuation will assess the mall's security value before registries can proceed.

news.title: Evergrande: China's indebted, delisted property behemoth
news.para: Evergrande, a major Chinese property developer, faced delisting from Hong Kong Stock Exchange. The company struggled with debt after new regulations in 2020. This situation reflects a broader downturn in China's property sector. The delisting highlights challenges in China's economy. Experts suggest China needs a new growth engine. The Evergrande collapse serves as a lesson for policymakers.

news.title: China's JD.Com unit, two other firms plan $1 billion Singapore REIT: Sources
news.para: JD Property, Partners Group, and EZA Hill are planning to launch a Singapore-based REIT potentially valued at over $1 billion, targeting industrial properties in Southeast Asia. The REIT, expected to list on the Singapore Exchange as early as next year, signals confidence in the region's REIT market. This move follows their joint acquisition of logistics assets from CapitaLand Ascendas REIT.

news.title: Germany's Aroundtown posts $677 million profit in H1 2025
news.para: Aroundtown, a major German landlord, reported a first-half profit of 578 million euros, a significant turnaround from the previous year's loss, driven by recovering property prices. While confirming its full-year guidance and seeing rental income growth, the company's shares dipped despite a positive analyst assessment.

news.title: Haryana abolishes stamp duty on purchase of 50 sq yards, 100 sq yards plots
news.para: Haryana Chief Minister Nayab Saini has abolished stamp duty on small residential plots in urban and rural areas, benefiting those under various housing schemes. This decision came in response to opposition concerns about increased collector rates, which Saini defended as a data-driven and transparent process. He also criticized the previous government's handling of collector rates, alleging favoritism towards builders.

news.title: Sri Lotus Developers and Realty's profit down 36% to ₹26 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Sri Lotus Developers and Realty Limited has announced its financial results. The company's consolidated net profit witnessed a decrease of 36 percent. It amounted to Rs 25.78 crore in the first quarter. Total income also experienced a dip, reaching Rs 68.09 crore. The company had recently launched its Initial Public Offering.

news.title: Protect land of petitioner, Telangana high court orders HYDRAA
news.para: The Telangana High Court intervened in a land dispute involving HYDRAA and two landowners, Jagal Reddy and Y Venkat Reddy, in Madhapur village. The court directed HYDRAA to remove its signboards from the disputed plots after landowners alleged illegal attempts to take possession and demolition of property without notice.

news.title: Transit-oriented development could transform Bengaluru traffic system
news.para: The state government will engage world-class private agencies through international bidding, moving away from relying solely on state-run institutions. Covering BBMP limits and beyond, over 500 sq km, the plan will utilise drone surveys, updated land-use maps, high-resolution images, and digital elevation models.

news.title: HC tells govt to issue circular to follow Madurai civic body model on property tax assessments
news.para: The Madras High Court, impressed by Madurai corporation's detailed action plan for property tax assessment, directed the state government to issue a circular. This circular instructs all corporations, municipalities, and town panchayats in Tamil Nadu to adopt Madurai's model. This action follows a PIL highlighting a significant property tax scam in Madurai, leading to substantial revenue loss.

news.title: Bihar to provide free land, interest subvention of up to ₹40 crore to investors under new policy: CM
news.para: Bihar government unveiled the 'Bihar Industrial Investment Promotion Package 2025' to boost industrial growth and create jobs. The policy offers free land allocation and interest subvention up to Rs 40 crore for investors. Units investing over Rs 100 crore or Fortune 500 companies can get free land.

news.title: Navsari civic body serves notices to 40 illegal under-construction sites
news.para: Navsari Municipal Corporation has initiated a crackdown on illegal construction. Notices were issued to 40 commercial and residential sites lacking valid permissions. The town planning department inspected 200 sites, demanding document submission within five days. Structures without approvals may face demolition. Ward-10 recorded the highest number of suspected illegal constructions.

news.title: Nazul land amnesty scheme extended; 5,000 leaseholders to benefit in Nagpur
news.para: The Maharashtra government has prolonged the special amnesty scheme for nazul lands in Nagpur and Amravati. This extension applies to lands leased for residential purposes. It is valid until July 31, 2026. The scheme allows conversion to freehold property at a reduced fee. Nagpur city has a significant number of nazul plots.
